b'I\xe2\x80\x99m now moving forward solo and ha e produced a record with my former band mate @adriancotamusic and we have finished my first full-length record since \xe2\x80\x98Free\xe2\x80\x99. A step forward on that path, but also a step back into my roots. Building on that independent discography I began at 18.'

b'The Tide was an awesome exploration that started as a trio that strictly jammed blues rock who eventually explored other sonic landscapes and we made a few cool EP projects that I\xe2\x80\x99m very proud of to this day.'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cFree\xe2\x80\x9d was my first step in that direction, following the path of musicians I grew up admiring that carved paths outside of the conventional popular music scene of the time. Ben Harper, Jack Johnson, Donavon Frankenreiter.'

b'A fair amount of you guys know that as an artist, I\xe2\x80\x99m independent. In my late teens I left my label and have been doing it that way ever since. Not particularly as an act of rebellion but out of a yearning for greater musical freedom and the ability to make what I truly wanted.'
